Vice President Joe Biden, Chair of the White House Task Force on the Middle Class, has released the Middle Class Task Force's Annual Report. The report outlines policy recommendations to address the challenges facing America's middle class. It includes proposals such as increasing the Child and Dependent Care Tax Credit, boosting funding for programs supporting caregivers, capping student loan payments, and enhancing retirement security. The report also highlights the Department of Labor's new regulations to protect workers' retirement savings. These regulations aim to prevent conflicts of interest and provide workers with expert investment advice. The Middle Class Task Force includes top-level administration agencies and councils that focus on issues impacting middle-class families.